At the home Victor-Gadbois you can offer a group of voluntary body care and assistance in the taking of food.
Palliative care is used if there are no other options.
To make dying more pleasant.
In Quebec there is a bed for palliative care on 11,700 inhabitants.
That's very little if you consider that one day we'll all die.
Here life is continued under the best possible conditions, explains Dr. Christiane Martel, one of the doctors of the home.
Both at the level of physical, emotional or spiritual comfort.
Depending on your wishes, you give the dying mouth care with Brandy or Pepsi.
Diabetic patients will no longer have to control their blood sugar levels.
