Following the first RM rockets, the Meteor-1 missile was developed between 1962 and 1965.
The rocket was designed as a two-stage rocket, its overall length was 510 cm and its initial weight was 32.5 kg.
Three types of rocket were developed (meteor-1A, -1B and -1C), which differ in the size of the transport space for scientific instruments.
