The maximum flight altitude was 37 km for all three types.
In the years 1965 to 1968, the Meteor-2 missile was developed in the Aviation Institute, whose first flight tests began in October 1970.
Meteor-2 had a take-off weight of 380 kg and was able to transport a payload of 10 kg to a height of about 60 km.
