During the day only the image of the Presidential Meeting without sound was transmitted with the message "private session, limited audio".
The few information circulated among the journalists was received by the press spokesmen of some of the unasoured governments present at the meeting, but not by the Peruvian press spokesperson.
The only document that was published during the day was the list of the participating presidents, which caused discomfort to the hundreds of journalists of various national and international media who demanded more information.
