"He was an original person and lived life fully," Gray explained in a communication.
Hagman was diagnosed with liver cirrhosis in 1992, and he admitted that he drank a lot over the years.
In 1995, a malignant tumour was detected in his liver, and he underwent transplantation.
In the years before "Dallas" Hagman became known on television as a nice guy in the years 1965 to 1970 with the Sitcom "Beautiful Jeannie" of the NBC television station.
There he played the astronaut Tony Nelson, whose life is put on his head when he met an attractive "jinn" (played by Barbara Eden), who will live with him at home.
